    # Do the sky combination

    my $outf = sprintf("sky_%s_%05d%s",$Frm->hdr("ORACUT"),$Grp->name,
                      $Frm->fitssuffix);
    _SKYCOMBINE_ OUT=$outf

    # Now file the output into an index

    _FILE_SKY_ NAME=$outf


=head1 NAME

_OFFSET_SKY_COMBINE_ -- Combine exposures in a group to form an offset sky
and file the result.

=head1 DESCRIPTION

The exposures from a group will be combined to form an offset sky. This can
be exposures that have been specially taken to provide a sky estimate or just
another target observations that are in a non-crowded region that can provide
a sky estimate for another more crowded region.

=head1 ARGUMENTS

None

=head1 NOTES

The output file will be called "sky_XXXXXXXX_YYYYY.fit" where XXXXXXXX is
the UT Date and YYYYY is the group name.

=head1 AUTHORS

JRL: Jim Lewis (CASU, IoA)

